mixin predictionModelForm(store = {})
	p.disclaimer.sans-seriff
		font(color='red') This risk-adjusted mortality estimate is recommended to be used for guidance in the overall conversation with the patient when choosing the most appropriate amputation level but not a recommendation for or against a specific amputation level.

	form(action="/predictionModel" method="POST" class="card")
		p.sans-seriff All parameters are required to derive an adjusted 1-year risk of mortality, reamputation, and probability of achieving basic and advanced mobility
		
		label(for="amputation_level") 
			font(size='+2') Amputation Level  
			br
			br
			select(name="amputation_level", id=amputation_level, size='1')
				option(value='')
				option(value='1') Transmetatarsal
				option(value='2') Transtibial
				option(value='3') Transfemoral
		
		br
		font(size='+2') Demographics

		label(for="age") How old is the patient (years)?    
			input(type='number', name='age', style='width: 100px;', placeholder="40-99")
		label(for="Gender") What is the patient's sex?
			select(name="Gender", size='1')
				option(value='')
				option(value='0') Female
				option(value='1') Male
		label(for="bmi") What is the patient's BMI (kg/m^2)?    
			input(type='number', name='bmi', style='width: 100px;', placeholder="ex. 24.1")
		label(for="race") What is the patient's race? (Currently, selecting white is the only option that changes calc values)
			select(name="race", size='1')
				option(value='')
				option(value='1') White
				option(value='2') Black
				option(value='3') Hispanic
				option(value='4') Other
		label(for="MaritalStatus") Is the patient married?
			select(name="MaritalStatus", size='1')
				option(value='')
				option(value='1') Yes
				option(value='0') No
		label(for="EducationStatus") Is the patient educated? (Currently Yes or No)
			select(name="EducationStatus", size='1')
				option(value='')
				option(value='1') Yes
				option(value='0') No
		label(for="functional_status") What has been the patient's functional status in the past 30 days prior to surgery?   
			select(name="functional_status", size='1')
				option(value='')
				option(value='1') Independent
				option(value='2') Partially Dependent
				option(value='3') Totally Dependent
			ul
				font(size='-2.5') <b>Independent</b>: The patient does not require assistance of nursing care, equipment or devices. This would include a person who is able to function independently with prosthesis, equipment, or devices.
			ul
				font(size='-2.5') <b>Partially dependent</b>: The patient requires the use of equipment or devices coupled with assistance from another person for some activities of daily living. Any patient coming from a nursing home setting who is not totally dependent would fall into this category, as would any patient who requires kidney dialysis or home ventilator support that requires chronic oxygen therapy yet maintains some independent functions.
			ul
				font(size='-2.5') <b>Totally dependent</b>: The patient cannot perform any activities of daily living for himself/herself. This would include a patient on an ICU/floor who is totally dependent upon nursing care, or a dependent nursing home patient. All patients with psychiatric illnesses should be evaluated for their ability to function with or without assistance with ADLs just as the non-psychiatric patient.

		br
		font(size='+2') Comorbidities

		label(for="heart_failure") Has the patient ever been diagnosed with congestive heart failure?   
			select(name="heart_failure", size='1')
				option(value='')
				option(value='1') Yes
				option(value='0') No
		label(for="dialysis") Is the patient currently on dialysis?   
			select(name="dialysis", size='1')
				option(value='')
				option(value='1') Yes
				option(value='0') No	
		label(for="Diabetes") Does the patient have Diabetes?
			select(name="Diabetes", size='1')
				option(value='')
				option(value='1') Yes
				option(value='0') No
		label(for="Revascularization") Does the patient have a history of a revascularization on the side of their amputation (this may include open, endo, or both)?
			select(name="Revascularization", size='1')
				option(value='')
				option(value='1') Yes
				option(value='0') No
		label(for="KidneyFailure") Has the patient had kidney failure?
			select(name="KidneyFailure", size='1')
				option(value='')
				option(value='1') Yes
				option(value='0') No
		label(for="COPD") Does the patient have COPD?
			select(name="COPD", size='1')
				option(value='')
				option(value='1') Yes
				option(value='0') No
		label(for="AnxietyDepression") Does the patient have Anxiety or Depression?
			select(name="AnxietyDepression", size='1')
				option(value='')
				option(value='1') Yes
				option(value='0') No
		label(for="RestGangrene") Does the patient currently experience rest pain or do they have gangrene (rest pain defined in the 3-days preceding amputation experiencing a more severe form of ischemic pain due to occlusive disease which occurs at rest and is manifested as a severe, unrelenting pain aggravated by elevation and often preventing sleep.  Gangrene defined as a marked skin discoloration and disruption indicative of death and decay of tissues in the extremities due to severe and prolonged ischemia.  Include patients with ischemic ulceration and/or tissue loss related to peripheral vascular disease)
			select(name="RestGangrene", size='1')
				option(value='')
				option(value='1') Yes
				option(value='0') No

		
		br
		font(size='+2') Laboratory Values

		label(for="blood_nitrogen") What is the patient’s most recent blood urea nitrogen (BUN) level (mg/dl)   
			input(type='number', name='blood_nitrogen', style='width: 100px;', placeholder="1-157")
		label(for="platelet_count") What is the patient's most recent platelet count (per mL)?   
			input(type='float', name='platelet_count', style='width: 100px;', placeholder="ex. 150,000")
		label(for="WBC") Do you have a white blood cell count of 11,000 or higher?
			select(name="WBC", size='1')
				option(value='')
				option(value='1') Yes
				option(value='0') No

		br
		font(size='+2') Health and Behavior

		label(for="Smoke") Does the patient smoke cigerattes?
			select(name="Smoke", size='1')
				option(value='')
				option(value='1') Yes
				option(value='0') No
		label(for="Alcohol") Does the patient drink Alcohol?
			select(name="Alcohol", size='1')
				option(value='')
				option(value='1') Yes
				option(value='0') No
		label(for="OutputAnticoagulants") Is the patient currently on outpatient anticoagulants?
			select(name="OutputAnticoagulants", size='1')
				option(value='')
				option(value='1') Yes
				option(value='0') No
		label(for="SelfRatedHealth") How does the patient rate their overall health (you need to give the patient options to select from)?
			select(name="SelfRatedHealth", size='1')
				option(value='')
				option(value='1') Good Health
				option(value='0') Bad Health
		center 
			input(type="submit" value="Predicted Risks" class="button" style='width: 50%;')